{{Top|leg|notoc=1}}
The '''Museum of Applied Photonics''' was a [[Museum/Legends|museum]] on [[Obroa-skai/Legends|Obroa-skai]], consisting of several [[Transparisteel/Legends|transparisteel]] and [[crystalplas]] towers.<ref name="SBS">''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]''</ref> When the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[First Battle of Obroa-skai|conquered]] the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], the building was one of a thousand left intact by the invaders, so they could further study [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] inhabitants. The building itself was taken by [[Warmaster]] [[Tsavong Lah]] as his personal base of operations.<ref name="enc">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref>

{{Noncanonstart|legends=1}}
During the spring break of [[Roan Novachez]]'s second [[Standard year/Legends|year]] at the [[Jedi academy]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], he visited Obroa-skai with his friend [[Pasha]] and [[Pasha's dad]]. On the first day of the trip, they took him to visit the Museum of Applied Photonics, but due to some mix-up, the museum's [[Security guard/Legends|security guard]] would not allow Roan inside and he was forced to wait in the museum's [[Foodstuff/Legends|food]] court while Pasha and his dad visited the museum.
{{Noncanonend}}

